#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_settings.rst:24
msgid ""
"Project Settings define first and foremost the properties of the final video "
"(a rescaling or output format change during the render process "
"notwithstanding). That includes the dimensions (e.g. 1920x1080), aspect "
"ratio (e.g. 16:9 or 9:16 or 4:3), frame rate (e.g. 30fps), color space, and "
"interlaced or progressive rendering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_settings.rst:29
msgid ""
"Depending on the project profile you chose, the :ref:`edit layout <ui-"
"workspace_layouts>` automatically switches to horizontal or vertical with "
"the :ref:`safe areas <ui_elements-monitor_icons>` adapting at the same time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_settings.rst:33
msgid ""
"Besides that, you can define where Kdenlive stores all project assets, how "
"many video and audio tracks there are initially (you can add or delete "
"tracks later as needed), whether or not Kdenlive should create proxy files "
"automatically and under what circumstances, and you can enter metadata like "
"author's name and copyright information which will be embedded in the "
"multimedia container during export/render."
msgstr ""

#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_settings.rst:35
msgid ""
"Here you also define the categories and colors for the timeline marker and "
"markers you can use in the timeline to structure your project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_settings.rst:37
msgid ""
"Once the project is underway, you can find here some statistics about your "
"project, like number and size of the clips, used versus unused, and about "
"the data cache. Kdenlive gives you full control over the use and utilization "
"of your assets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_settings.rst:39
msgid ""
"The project settings dialog is opened every time a new project is created (:"
"menuselection:`Menu --> File --> New`), or via :menuselection:`Menu --> File "
"--> Project Settings`."
msgstr ""

